quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  16,111,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day ňĻwhenňļ every soul will come pleading for itself, and each will be paid in full for what it did, and none will be wronged"
  16,112,"And Allah sets forth the example of a society which was safe and at ease, receiving its provision in abundance from all directions. But its people met Allah‚Äôs favours with ingratitude, so Allah made them taste the clutches of hunger and fear for their misdeeds"
  16,113,"A messenger of their own actually did come to them, but they denied him. So the torment overtook them while they persisted in wrongdoing"
  16,114,"So eat from the good, lawful things which Allah has provided for you, and be grateful for Allah‚Äôs favours, if you ňĻtrulyňļ worship Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  16,115,"He has only forbidden you ňĻto eatňļ carrion, blood, swine,¬†and what is slaughtered in the name of any other than Allah. But if someone is compelled by necessity‚ÄĒneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate need‚ÄĒthen surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,116,"Do not falsely declare with your tongues, ‚ÄúThis is lawful, and that is unlawful,‚ÄĚ ňĻonlyňļ fabricating lies against Allah. Indeed, those who fabricate lies against Allah will never succeed"
  16,117,"ňĻIt is onlyňļ a brief enjoyment, then they will suffer a painful punishment"
  16,118,"To the Jews, We have forbidden what We related to you before.¬†We did not wrong them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  16,119,"As for those who commit evil ignorantly ňĻor recklesslyňļ, then repent afterwards and mend their ways, then your Lord is surely All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,120,"Indeed, Abraham was a model of excellence: devoted to Allah, ňĻperfectlyňļ upright‚ÄĒnot a polytheist‚ÄĒ"
  16,121,ňĻutterlyňļ grateful for Allah‚Äôs favours. ňĻSoňļ He chose him and guided him to the Straight Path
  16,122,"We blessed him with all goodness in this world,¬†and in the Hereafter he will certainly be among the righteous"
  16,123,"Then We revealed to you ňĻO Prophet, sayingňļ: ‚ÄúFollow the faith of Abraham, the upright, who was not one of the polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  16,124,ňĻHonouringňļ the Sabbath was ordained only for those who disputed about Abraham.¬†And surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their disputes
  16,125,"Invite ňĻallňļ to the Way of your Lord with wisdom and kind advice, and only debate with them in the best manner. Surely your Lord ňĻaloneňļ knows best who has strayed from His Way and who is ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  16,126,"If you retaliate, then let it be equivalent to what you have suffered. But if you patiently endure, it is certainly best for those who are patient"
  16,127,"Be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ, for your patience is only with Allah‚Äôs help. Do not grieve over those ňĻwho disbelieveňļ, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  16,128,Surely Allah is with those who shun evil and who do good ňĻdeedsňļ